
// This Hyperlambda code throws an exception with a message retrieved from the HTTP POST response, specifically from the "error" message in the response content. The exception is marked as public, meaning it will be visible to the client, and the HTTP status code of the exception is set to the status code from the HTTP POST response.
throw:x:@http.post/*/content/*/error/*/message
   public:bool:true
   status:x:@http.post
